{
  "stem": "7157.2",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This was the situation where the Polish underground-- you know, there was always an underground in, in Poland.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was, it was made up of Polish people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was made up of a lot of Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And in Warsaw, of course, the underground was very strong.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Every once in a while, you'd hear that there was a big explosion at a German headquarters, because the underground did something.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "A train was derailed, or something like this.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Just to back up a bit, when we first got to Warsaw, you know, the Warsaw ghetto fire.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They burned the Warsaw ghetto.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I remember we were, like, half a mile or a quarter of a mile from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We actually saw the flames and saw the people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I didn't see this, but my mother said she saw people crawling out of sewers, Jews crawling out of sewers, that somehow escaped this fire.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But a lot of these-- the point I'm making-- a lot of these Jews then went into the woods and hid and became part of the underground, the resistance movement.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So in 1944, as the Russians were approaching towards Warsaw, the Germans decided-- the Polish underground, I should say, decided to rise up against the Germans, to capture their own capital, to capture their city.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
